SIMPLE: executor
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Executor
<hw>Ex*ec"u*tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>executor</ets>, <ets>exsecutor</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>ex⟦eacute⟧cuteur</ets>. Cf. <er>Executer</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One who executes or performs; a doer; <as>as, an <ex>executor</ex>
of baseness</as>.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An executioner.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Delivering o'er to <qex>executors</qex> paw<?/⟦br⟧
The lazy, yawning drone.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>The person appointed by a testator
to execute his will, or to see its provisions carried into effect, after
his decease.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>\'d8Executor de son tort</b></col> <ety>[Of., executor of
his own wrong]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld>, <cd>a stranger who intermeddles
without authority in the distribution of the estate of a deceased
person.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Executorial</ent>⟦br⟧
